00:17:16.579 --> 00:17:21.790
on this one moment when, you know, the ultimate
future that they though was going to happen,

00:17:21.790 --> 00:17:25.870
it doesn't happen and it's because of that
one thing that happens without spoiling too

00:17:25.870 --> 00:17:30.820
much people; we're interested in the show
but haven't seen it yet. And you know, basically,

00:17:30.820 --> 00:17:36.540
things are very different afterwards as results
of that. And approve that, I wasn't like making

00:17:36.540 --> 00:17:41.570
all of the stuff up. If you look closely in
one of the episodes from season three, Arthur

00:17:41.570 --> 00:17:47.660
Petrelli who's, like he's the bad guy of the
show in that season. He's actually holding

00:17:47.660 --> 00:17:53.590
a copy of one of Nietzsche's books: "Thus
